## Session History — What We Did

### Phase 1: Bug Fixes (ORION 2.0 Foundation)

**Problem:** Session tracking was broken — new sessions returned ID 0, messages weren't saving to correct sessions, and chat history didn't restore properly.

**Fixes Applied:**
| File | Fix |
|------|-----|
| `CORE/memory-engine.js` | Changed `createSession` to use `SELECT MAX(id)` instead of `last_insert_rowid()` (which returned 0) |
| `preload.js` | Fixed async handling so session ID is properly awaited before use |
| `preload.js` | Added fallback: return ID `1` if no session exists |
| `main.js` | Added fallback: auto-create session if none exists on `getCurrentSessionId` |
| `main.js` | Added `[Main]` debug logging throughout chat flow |
| `preload.js` | Added `[Preload]` debug logging throughout chat flow |
| `renderer.js` | Added `[Renderer]` debug logging throughout chat flow |
| `CORE/ai-brain.js` | Added `[AIBrain]` debug logging throughout chat flow |
| `CORE/memory-engine.js` | Added `[Memory]` debug logging for session ops |

